r 2014 |ref=C8 }}\n*{{cite book |author=DB |authorlink=Thomas Chatterton |year=1769 |chapter=Godred Crovan. A Poem. Composed by Dopnal Syrric, Scheld of Godred Crovan, King of the Isle of Man |title=Town and Country Magazine |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qjI3AAAAYAAJ |publisher=A. Hamilton |location=London |pages=425\u2013428 |ref=D12 }}\n*{{cite journal |year=1931 |editor-last=Dobbs |editor-first=ME |title=The Ban-Shenchus |url=http://catalogue.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/cb34418441f |journal=[[Revue Celtique]] |volume=48 |pages=163\u2013234 |ref=D13 }}\n*{{cite book |year=n.d. |editor1-last=Elrington |editor1-first=CR |editor1-link=Charles Richard Elrington |editor2-last=Todd |editor2-first=JH |editor2-link=James Henthorn Todd |title=The Whole Works of the Most Rev. James Ussher, D.D., Lord Archbishop of Armagh, and Primate of All Ireland |url=https://archive.org/details/lifeofjamesusshe04elriuoft |volume=4 |publisher=Hodges and Smith |location=Dublin |ref=E1 }}\n*{{cite book |year=1990 |editor-last=Evans |editor-first=DS |title=A Mediaeval Prince of Wales: The Life of Gruffudd ap Cynan |publisher=Llanerch Enterprises |location= |isbn=0947992472 |ref=E3 }}\n*{{cite book |year=1854 |editor-last=Forester |editor-first=T |title=The Ecclesiastical History of England and Normandy, by Ordericus Vitalus |url=https://archive.org/details/ecclesiasticalhi02ordeuoft |series=[[Bohn's Antiquarian Library]] |volume=2 |publisher=[[Henry G. Bohn]] |location=London |ref=F3 }}\n*{{cite book |year=1883 |editor-last=Gill |editor-first=JF |title=The Statutes of the Isle of Man |volume=1 |url=https://archive.org/details/statutesisleman00mangoog |publisher=Eyre and Spottiswoode |ref=G1 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Hudson |first=BT |author-link=Benjamin Hudson |year=1996 |title=Prophecy of Berch\u00e1n: Irish and Scottish High-Kings of the Early Middle Ages |series=Contributions to the Study of World History |publisher=[[Greenwood Press]] |location=Westport, CT |isbn=0-313-29567-0 |issn=0885-9159 |ref=H15 }}\n*{{cite web |year=n.d. |url=http://image.ox.ac.uk/show?collection=jesus&manuscript=ms111 |title=Jesus College MS. 111 |website=Early Manuscripts at Oxford University |publisher=Oxford Digital Library |accessdate=24 November 2016 |ref=J9 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Johnston |first=D |authorlink=Duncan Johnston (songwriter) |year=1997 |origyear=1938 |title=Cronan nan Tonn |publisher=Dun Eisdein |location=Inverness |ref=J4 }}\n*{{cite book |year=1910 |editor-last=Jones |editor-first=A |title=The History of Gruffydd ap Cynan: The Welsh Text with Translation, Introduction, and Notes |url=https://archive.org/details/historyofgrufydd00joneuoft |publisher=Sherratt & Hughes |location=Manchester |ol=7100180M |ref=J1 }}\n*{{cite book |year=1845 |editor-last=Le Prevost |editor-first=A |title=Orderici Vitalis Histori\u00e6 Ecclesiastic\u00e6 Libri Tredecim |url=https://archive.org/details/ordericivitalish03ordeuoft |volume=3 |publisher=Julium Renouard et Socios |location=Paris |ref=L2 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Livingston |first=W |authorlink=William Livingston (poet) |year=1850 |title=The Vindication of the Celtic Character |url=https://archive.org/details/vindicationcelt00unkngoog |publisher=Joseph Blair |location=Greenock |ref=L8 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Livingston |first=W |year=1882 |title=Duain Agus Orain |url=https://archive.org/details/duainagusorainle00macd |publisher=Archibald Sinclair |location=Glasgow |ol=24345305M |ref=L9 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Moore |first=AW |author-link=Arthur William Moore |year=1891 |title=The Folk-Lore of the Isle of Man |url=https://archive.org/details/folkloreofisleof00moor |publisher=[[D. Nutt]] |location=London |ol=24828867M |ref=M29 }}\n*{{cite book |year=1874a |editor1-last=Munch |editor1-first=PA |editor1-link=Peter Andreas Munch |editor2-last=Goss |editor2-first=A |editor2-link=Alexander Goss |title=Chronica Regvm Manni\u00e6 et Insvlarvm: The Chronicle of Man and the Sudreys |url=https://archive.org/details/chronicaregvmma00gossg