ch, Property, and Conflict in Wales, AD 600\u20131100 |url=https://journals.library.wales/view/1073091/1082967/412 |journal=[[The Welsh History Review]] |volume=18 |number=3 |pages=387\u2013406 |issn=0043-2431 |eissn=0083-792X |hdl=10107/1082967 |hdl-access=free |ref=D15 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Davies |first=S |year=2014 |origyear=2004 |title=War and Society in Medieval Wales, 633\u20131283: Welsh Military Institutions |series=Studies in Welsh History |publisher=University of Wales Press |location=Cardiff |isbn=978-1-78316-142-3 |ref=D27 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Downham |first=C |year=2004 |chapter=England and the Irish-Sea Zone in the Eleventh Century |editor-last=Gillingham |editor-first=J |editor-link=John Gillingham |title=Anglo-Norman Studies |volume=26 |publisher=[[The Boydell Press]] |location=Woodbridge |pages=55\u201373 |isbn=1-84383-072-8 |issn=0954-9927 |ref=D7 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Downham |first=C |year=2005 |chapter=Fine Gall |editor-last=Duffy |editor-first=S |title=Medieval Ireland: An Encyclopedia |publisher=Routledge |location=New York |pages=170\u2013171 |isbn=0-415-94052-4 |ref=D11 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Downham |first=C |year=2013a |chapter=Living on the Edge: Scandinavian Dublin in the Twelfth Century |title=No Horns on Their Helmets? Essays on the Insular Viking-Age |series=Celtic, Anglo-Saxon, and Scandinavian Studies |publisher=Centre for Anglo-Saxon Studies and The Centre for Celtic Studies, [[University of Aberdeen]] |location=Aberdeen |pages=157\u2013178 |issn=2051-6509 |isbn=978-0-9557720-1-6 |ref=D19 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Downham |first=C |year=2013b |chapter=The Historical Importance of Viking-Age Waterford |title=No Horns on Their Helmets? Essays on the Insular Viking-Age |series=Celtic, Anglo-Saxon, and Scandinavian Studies |publisher=Centre for Anglo-Saxon Studies and The Centre for Celtic Studies, University of Aberdeen |location=Aberdeen |pages=129\u2013155 |issn=2051-6509 |isbn=978-0-9557720-1-6 |ref=D29 }}\n*{{cite book |last=Dow